raceComments: {"comment":"5. AMLETO has needed time to mature, and is getting out to a suitable trip third up from a spell after a pair of solid fourth-place finishes at Caulfield to open this season. He slides down in class and is ready to post an overdue win. 4. SO BRAVE produced a big finish from near last to score here in his penultimate start, and then was fourth in a tougher field at Caulfield 9 days ago. He is already looking for more ground, but with the advantage of the pole position, he will be right in the finish here. 10. SAXON BEAUTY has not put in a bad performance this season, and gave a great sight in front at Cranbourne just over a fortnight ago, before finishing second. She is nicely placed in this, and if she doesn't have to use up too much energy early on, then she will produce her usual honest effort. 11. FAREWELL TO EIRE settled closer than usual to the pace last time out on this track, and stuck on bravely to finish runner-up by a head. She cops a wide gate, but won't be far away.","runners":[5,4,10,11],"exclusive":true}
